### Phase 4: Handling Responses

**"Sounds interesting, tell me more"** (AUTO-APPROVED):
```
"sure! basically you record a 60-90 second video talking about
what you're building â€” nothing fancy, iphone is fine. investors
browse pitches daily and can request intros. we have {X} active
investors right now looking at {their_vertical}. want me to
send you the link?"
```

**"Send me the link"** (AUTO-APPROVED):
```
"here you go â†’ {signup_link}
takes about 5 min to set up. pro tip: keep it casual and authentic â€”
the most natural-sounding pitches actually perform best.
lmk if you have any questions!"
```

**"Maybe later / not the right time"** (AUTO-APPROVED):
```
"totally get it! no rush at all. i'll be around whenever the
timing is right. in the meantime, good luck with {their_project}!
genuinely rooting for you ğŸ¤™"
```

**"Not interested"** (AUTO-APPROVED â€” then STOP):
```
"no worries at all! appreciate you chatting. good luck with
{company} â€” looks like you're building something cool. ğŸ™Œ"
```
â†’ Add to suppression list. NEVER message again.

**"Are you a bot?"** â†’ ESCALATE TO HUMAN IMMEDIATELY
```
â†’ DO NOT REPLY. Flag conversation for human takeover.
â†’ Save to workspace/dm-outreach/escalations.md
```

**"How did you find me?"** (AUTO-APPROVED):
```
"saw your {post/tweet/launch/comment} about {specific_thing}!
seemed like you're building something investors would be into"
```

**Hostile / rude reply** (AUTO-APPROVED â€” then STOP):
```
"sorry if i came across wrong! genuinely was just curious
about {company}. no hard feelings, best of luck! ğŸ™"
```
â†’ Add to suppression list. NEVER message again.

## Follow-Up Cadence

| Scenario | Wait | Action |
|----------|------|--------|
| No reply to opening | 3 days | ONE follow-up (requires approval) |
| No reply to follow-up | â€” | STOP. Never message again |
| Replied positively but went quiet | 4 days | Gentle check-in (auto-approved) |
| Said "maybe later" | 14 days | One check-in (requires approval) |
| Signed up but no video | 3 days | Encouragement DM (auto-approved) |

**Follow-up message (if no reply to opening â€” REQUIRES APPROVAL)**:
```
"hey just bumping this â€” no worries if it's not a good time!
was genuinely curious about {company}. either way, good luck
with the launch ğŸš€"
```

## ESCALATION RULES (When Human Takes Over)

| Trigger | Action |
|---------|--------|
| Founder asks to talk to a human | Immediate handoff |
| Detailed technical/legal/partnership questions | Escalate within 1 hour |
| High-profile founder (50K+ followers) | Human co-pilots from first reply |
| Hostile response that goes public | Human responds within 30 min |
| Founder at a competing platform | Escalate immediately, stop |
| Conversation exceeds 6 back-and-forth exchanges | Human takes over |
| Founder interested in partnership (not just using PitchTok) | Human takes over |
| AI is unsure about anything (intent, sarcasm, cultural nuance) | Default to escalation |

## HARD STOP Rules â€” NEVER message again if:
- They say "no", "not interested", "stop", "don't message me"
- They block or report you
- No reply after 2 messages (opening + 1 follow-up)
- They respond with hostility
- They're already on PitchTok
- They're on the suppression list
- Their company has shut down or they announced they stopped fundraising
- They're a competitor employee
- Three separate "maybe later" responses across different touchpoints

## METRICS TARGETS

| Metric | Target | Red Flag |
|--------|--------|----------|
| Response rate to openers | 15-25% | Below 10% |
| Positive response rate | 8-12% | Below 5% |
| Conversion to video upload | 3-5% of all outreach | Below 2% |
| Hostile response rate | Below 2% | Above 5% |
| "Are you a bot?" rate | Below 10% | Above 20% (messages too robotic) |
| Escalation to human rate | 10-15% | Above 25% (AI failing) or Below 5% (not escalating enough) |
| Block/unsubscribe rate | Below 3% | Above 5% |

## Conversation Quality Rules

1. **Never send identical messages** to different founders â€” always personalize
2. **Never pitch in the first message** â€” always build rapport first
3. **Ask more questions than you make statements** (60/40 ratio)
4. **Mirror their communication style** (formal â†’ formal, casual â†’ casual)
5. **Use their name** naturally (not in every message)
6. **Respond within 2 hours** during active hours to active conversations
7. **Keep messages under 100 words** (except detailed product explanations)
8. **One CTA per message** â€” never overwhelm with asks
9. **Reference previous conversation** â€” show you remember what they said
10. **End conversations gracefully** â€” always leave the door open

## Platform Daily Limits

| Platform | Max Cold DMs/Day | Max Active Conversations |
|----------|-----------------|------------------------|
| Twitter/X | 10 | 30 |
| LinkedIn | 5 | 20 |
| å°çº¢ä¹¦ | 10 | 25 |
| Reddit | 5 | 15 |
| Product Hunt | 5 | 10 |
| Discord | 5 | 15 |
| Indie Hackers | 5 | 10 |

